### Identification

This document contains a high-level view of the System for Award Management (SAM) Data Dictionary and directs the reader to various other documents for a more detailed picture of the data elements found within SAM.

### System Overview

The System for Award Management (SAM) integrated the Contract Opportunities, Assistance Listings, Entity Information, Contract Data, Wage Determination, Entity Reporting, Responsibilities and Qualifications, and Federal Hierarchy. Combining these legacy systems streamlined business processes, eliminated data redundancies, and improved regulatory compliance.

SAM.gov unifies the government-wide award management systems. If you have the proper roles in SAM, you can register to do business with the U.S. government, update or renew your entity registration, check the status of an entity registration, manage exclusion records, manage user roles, search for entity registrations and exclusion records, and use entity registration and exclusion data.

This data dictionary addresses the data elements associated with the business processes required to manage an entity's Core Data, Assertions, Representations and Certifications, Points of Contact, and the management of Exclusion records.

### Document Organization

This Data Dictionary provides overall listing and descriptions of SAM Entity Management and Exclusion data fields at a high level. Using this document allows you to view the characteristics of data elements and what each is used for. This document includes field definitions and characteristics. The field lengths are the application-limited input lengths. The corresponding extract output lengths may be larger to accommodate migrated data.

