## SAM Field Definitions

### 820s Request Flag
- **Type:** Drop-Down
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The flag that indicates whether the entity wants to receive Remittance Advice Notices (820s) through the Value-Added Network (VAN) provider. The user selects "Yes" or "No".

### ABA Routing Number
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 50
- **Definition:** The routing transit number assigned by the American Banker's Association (ABA) for a U.S. financial institution. In SAM, this number must be the Electronic Funds Transfer (EFT) ABA Routing Number, not the Wire Transfer ABA number.

### Account Number
- **Type:** Alphanumeric with Special Characters
- **Length:** 20
- **Definition:** The U.S. financial institution account number at which the entity receives EFT payments.

### Account Type
- **Type:** Drop-Down
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The entity's financial account type. The user selects "Checking" or "Savings".

### Accounting Station
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 6
- **Definition:** For U.S. government entities, the Accounting Station (Fiscal Station Number) is a six-digit number that identifies the activity which is responsible for performing the official accounting and reporting for the funds.

### ACH Email
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 80
- **Definition:** A contact email address for the Automated Clearing House (ACH) Coordinator at the entity's U.S. financial institution.

### ACH Fax
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 30
- **Definition:** The fax number for the ACH Coordinator or Department at the entity's financial institution.

### ACH Non-U.S. Phone
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 30
- **Definition:** The phone number for the ACH Coordinator or Department at the entity's financial institution if it is located outside of the U.S.

### ACH U.S. Phone
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 30
- **Definition:** The phone number for the ACH Coordinator or Department at the entity's financial institution if it is located in the U.S.

### Active Date
- **Type:** Date
- **Length:** 8
- **Definition:** The date the exclusion record became active. This may be different than the date the exclusion record was created.

### Additional Comments
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 1,000
- **Definition:** Free-text field where the U.S. government official managing the exclusion record can add additional notes or a description regarding the exclusion. This field can be used for specific agency legislation citations.

### Address Line 1
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 150
- **Definition:** The first line of an address. The following characters are not accepted: `;`, `[`, `]`, `"`, `{`, `}`, `!`, `@`, `$`, `^`, `*`, `=`. Consecutive instances of the following characters are also not accepted: `..`, `++`, `--`, `''`.

### Address Line 2
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 150
- **Definition:** The second line of an address. The following characters are not accepted: `;`, `[`, `]`, `"`, `{`, `}`, `!`, `@`, `$`, `^`, `*`, `=`. Consecutive instances of the following characters are also not accepted: `..`, `++`, `--`, `''`.

### Address Type
- **Type:** Alpha
- **Length:** 20
- **Definition:** Indicates which address type is captured. Address Type codes include:

| Code | Name |
|------|------|
| X5 | Alternate Exclusion Address |
| X6 | EVS Address |
| X7 | DoDAAC Address |
| DM | Domestic Parent Address (Intermediate Parent) |
| GL | Ultimate Parent Address |
| HQ | Headquarters Parent Address (Intermediate Parent) |
| IR | Taxpayer Address |
| FE | Mailing Address |
| OA | Other Address |
| PA | Physical Address |
| X8 | POC Address |
| B3 | Previous Business Address |
| X9 | Primary Exclusion Address |
| RI | Remittance Address |

### Agency Code
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 4
- **Definition:** The U.S. Government Agency identifier aligned to the federal hierarchy. The agency codes were originally sourced from the Federal Procurement Data System (FPDS) and the NIST 800-87 listing.

### Agency Location Code
- **Type:** Drop-Down
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The Agency Location Code is used to identify accounting reports and documents prepared by or for agency accounting stations and disbursing offices, e.g. eight-digit agency accounting station code, four-digit disbursing office symbol, and three-digit Treasury disbursing center symbol. This eight-digit code corresponds to the registering office. The Agency Location Code is provided by the Treasury IPAC system. The user selects from a list of ALCs populated based on the Department Code selected.

### Agency Parent
- **Type:** Alpha
- **Length:** 10
- **Definition:** The name of the immediate parent of the excluding agency. This may be used to determine the Department under which the exclusion record falls.

### Architect-Engineer Responses
- **Type:** N/A
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The Architect and Engineering Responses provided during the Representations & Certifications part of an entity registration are used to complete the Standard Form (SF) 330 Part II for architect-engineer contracts. A-E Responses only apply to entities who selected one or more of the relevant NAICS Codes (541310, 541320, 541330, 541360, 541370, 541410, and 541620). The elements associated with these responses are detailed in the Full User Guides found within SAM Help (Federal User Guide Section 4.5.3 and Non-Federal User Guide Section 4.4.3).

### Attachment
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 50
- **Definition:** The pre-signed URL to access the attachment in R/Q page under Other Responsibility and Integrity Information.

### Authorization Date
- **Type:** Date
- **Length:** 8
- **Definition:** The effective date of an entity's EFT account authorization. The Authorization Date will be pre-filled by the system as the date a registration was created/updated. The Authorization Date must be present if an ABA Routing Number/financial institute was entered.

### Average Annual Receipts
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 15
- **Definition:** The average yearly receipts for the past five years for the location being registered rounded to the nearest dollar. This number must be less than or equal to the Total Receipts number.

### Average Number of Employees
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 25
- **Definition:** The number of worldwide employees for all affiliate, branches, etc. for an entity. Its value must be equal to or greater than the Location Number of Employees. Users must enter a value of 0 or greater.

### Barrels Capacity
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 15
- **Definition:** The number of Barrels per Day of Petroleum Refining if the entity selected NAICS Code 324110 as one of its NAICS offerings. This number will be compared against the SBA's small business size standard table to determine whether the company meets the small business concern threshold for this NAICS.

### Bonding Level Type
- **Type:** Multi-Select
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The type of bonding level selected by an entity including their registration on the Disaster Response Registry. Possible values:

| Code | Name |
|------|------|
| BL1 | Construction Bonding Level, Per Contract (dollars) |
| BL2 | Construction Bonding Level, Aggregate (dollars) |
| BL3 | Service Bonding Level, Per Contract (dollars) |
| BL4 | Service Bonding Level, Aggregate (dollars) |

### Bonding Level Value
- **Type:** Numeric
- **Length:** 22
- **Definition:** The dollar value (per contract or aggregate) of a Service or Construction Bond. This is used in the Disaster Response Registry.

### Bonding to Bid Flag
- **Type:** Drop-Down
- **Length:** N/A
- **Definition:** The flag that determines whether the entity requires bonding to bid on contracts. User selects "Yes" or "No". This is used in the Disaster Response Registry.

### Entity Start Date
- **Type:** Date
- **Length:** 8
- **Definition:** The date the entity was started or acquired. The format is MM/DD/YYYY (example: 01/01/1995) and must be today's date or earlier.

### Business Types
- **Type:** Alphanumeric
- **Length:** 2
- **Definition:** The different business types that can classify an entity. Some are set by external parties. Most are self-selected by the registrant.

